The clean path is to make the ECS renderer a deferred renderer by default: create owned G-buffer frame targets, draw scene materials into that framebuffer, then run a composite pass into the swapchain. I’m also going to add a small command-list API to explicitly end the current graphics render pass before transitioning the G-buffer for sampling, instead of relying on a side effect.

I’m making the render-pass boundary explicit in the core command-list contract first. That keeps the deferred pass transition legal and avoids smuggling pass ending through an unrelated compute or graphics state change.

